<p>Returns the size of a variable / array / string of a fixed length.
This is a compile-time function, so it will only reflect the size at the declaration
of the variable.
<p>Example:
<code>
var
  myString : string ="beep";
  i := sizeof(myString); // sizeof(myString) is replaced with "4" compile time

</code>
<p>
Example 2:
<code>
var
   arr: array[10] of integer;
   b : byte = sizeof(arr); // 20

</code>

